Sekerbank Sells $93 Million in Problem Loans to Girisim Varlik

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-03-26T13:10:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-26/sekerbank-sells-93-million-in-problem-loans-to-girisim-varlik.html
Sekerbank TAS (SKBNK) , a Turkish lender,
sold 144 million liras ($93 million) in non-performing loans for
12 million liras, the bank said in a statement to the stock
exchange after the market closed yesterday.  The loans were purchased by asset manager Girisim Varlik
Yonetim AS and payment was received March 24, Sekerbank said.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Benjamin Harvey at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net  